  <section id="privacypolicy-section1" class="privacypolicy-section">
    <h2><i class="fas fa-database"></i> 1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect various types of information to operate, maintain, secure, and improve our Services.</p>
    <h3>1.1 Information You Provide Directly</h3>
    <p>We may collect personal information that you voluntarily submit when you register an account, submit support tickets, join our Discord, apply for staff positions, or participate in community activities.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Full name (if provided)</li>
      <li>Username / In-game name</li>
      <li>Email address</li>
      <li>Discord ID or username</li>
      <li>Phone number (only if voluntarily provided)</li>
      <li>Any message, feedback, or data you submit</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>1.2 Gameplay and Game Server Information</h3>
    <p>When you join our game servers, we automatically collect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>IP address and connection data</li>
      <li>Join/leave timestamps and server region</li>
      <li>Chat logs and commands executed</li>
      <li>Player actions, bans, warnings, and penalties</li>
      <li>Anti-cheat alerts and player reports</li>
      <li>Gameplay analytics (kills, deaths, activities)</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>1.3 Automatic Website Data</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>IP address, browser type, and operating system</li>
      <li>Device type and pages visited</li>
      <li>Cookies, session identifiers, and referring URLs</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>1.4 Third-Party Data</h3>
    <p>We may receive information through integrated services like Discord API, Google Analytics, payment processors, and game server management plugins.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="privacypolicy-section2" class="privacypolicy-section">
    <h2><i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> 2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <h3>2.1 Service Operation & Account Management</h3>
    <p>Operating game servers, managing ranks and permissions, ensuring stable performance, and processing support requests.</p>
    <h3>2.2 Moderation, Safety & Rule Enforcement</h3>
    <p>We use gameplay and server logs to detect cheating, investigate reports, review chat logs, apply disciplinary actions, and maintain a safe gaming environment.</p>
    <h3>2.3 Communication</h3>
    <p>We may contact you to respond to support requests, notify you of appeals or issues, provide service updates, and send security alerts.</p>
    <div class="privacypolicy-highlight-box"><p><strong>Note:</strong> We do not send spam or marketing messages without your consent.</p></div>
    <h3>2.4 Security & Legal Compliance</h3>
    <p>Preventing fraud, detecting suspicious activity, complying with legal obligations, and protecting community members.</p>
    <h3>2.5 Website Improvement</h3>
    <p>Understanding user interactions, improving performance, fixing bugs, and optimizing user experience.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="privacypolicy-section3" class="privacypolicy-section">
    <h2><i class="fas fa-balance-scale"></i> 3. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)</h2>
    <p>If you are located in the EU or any region under GDPR, we process your information based on:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Consent:</strong> When you voluntarily provide data</li>
      <li><strong>Contractual necessity:</strong> When data is required to provide Services</li>
      <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> For moderation, security, and community management</li>
      <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> When required to comply with the law</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="privacypolicy-section4" class="privacypolicy-section">
    <h2><i class="fas fa-cookie-bite"></i> 4. Cookies & Tracking Technologies</h2>
    <p>We use cookies and similar technologies to maintain sessions, store preferences, measure website usage, and improve performance.</p>
    <div class="privacypolicy-highlight-box"><p>You may disable cookies via your browser settings; however, some features may not function properly.</p></div>
  </section>

  <section id="privacypolicy-section5" class="privacypolicy-section">
    <h2><i class="fas fa-share-alt"></i> 5. Data Sharing & Disclosure</h2>
    <div class="privacypolicy-highlight-box"><p><strong>We do not sell, rent, or trade personal information.</strong></p></div>
    <p>We may share data only in these circumstances:</p>
    <h3>5.1 Service Providers</h3>
    <p>Trusted third-party providers who assist with hosting, analytics, security, payment processing, and Discord integrations.</p>
    <h3>5.2 Moderation and Community Management</h3>
    <p>Authorized staff may access logs and player information for rule enforcement, investigations, and security monitoring. All staff must uphold confidentiality.</p>
    <h3>5.3 Legal Requirements</h3>
    <p>We may disclose information to comply with laws, respond to law enforcement, or protect rights and safety.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="privacypolicy-section6" class="privacypolicy-section">
    <h2><i class="fas fa-lock"></i> 6. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We implement reasonable security measures including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access-restricted databases</li>
      <li>Secure server configuration</li>
      <li>Encryption where appropriate</li>
      <li>Regular security audits and monitoring</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="privacypolicy-highlight-box"><p>While we strive to protect all information, no system is entirely secure. You use our Services at your own risk.</p></div>
  </section>

  <section id="privacypolicy-section7" class="privacypolicy-section">
    <h2><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> 7. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>We retain your information only as long as necessary for providing Services, moderation needs, legal compliance, and dispute resolution.</p>
    <p>Gameplay logs, chat logs, and moderation records may be retained for extended periods to maintain community integrity.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="privacypolicy-section8" class="privacypolicy-section">
    <h2><i class="fas fa-user-shield"></i> 8. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>Depending on your region, you may have the right to:</p>
